TOP READ in the past 7 days

Epilepsy and EEG Feature Prominently in Determining
Cobalamin Congenital Deficiency
Seizures associated with failure to thrive occurring
in infants during their first year of life may be due
to cobalamin deficiency. Evaluation of plasma amino
acids and urinary acid organic analysis in these and
other children with convulsive status epilepticus will
help lead to a diagnosis. Cobalamin (Cbl) is an inborn
error of intracellular Cbl ... Full Story

messages.msgSnippet: Deb you are such a blessing!!  I am sitting here dog tired from play rehearsals. (I am doing my first Shakespeare show and we open tonight so this week has
messages.messageBody:
Deb you are such a blessing!! I am sitting here dog tired from play
rehearsals. (I am doing my first Shakespeare show and we open tonight so this
week has been "hell week" with rehearsals every night until late and adding
all the tech stuff like costumes, make-up, lights, and sound.) With one
short "swirl" you've picked me up and made me appreciate where I am Right Now!

Here in Western North Carolina we are experiencing a cold front. I say
Hurrah! This means it won't be 85 when I get to the show tonight and I won't
sweat buckets in the setting sun wearing all the costume pieces. Today it is
only supposed to be in the mid-70s. I can deal with that!!

Thanks again, and if I come help clean the pool will Dylan make some more
frozen soy dessert? Strawberrry is my favorite!

DiAnna, smiling and rejoicing in how much my girls do for me every day
